In [34]:
import cv2


val_images = []
val_labels = []

test_images = []
test_labels = []

input_path = 'chest_xray_data/chest_xray/'

for i in (['val', 'test']):    
    for opt in ['/NORMAL/', '/PNEUMONIA/']:
        for img in (os.listdir(input_path + str(i) + opt)):
            img = plt.imread(input_path + str(i) + opt + img)
            img = cv2.resize(img, (150, 150))
            img = np.dstack([img, img, img])
            img = img.astype('float32') / 255
            if i == 'val':
                if opt =='/NORMAL/':
                    label = 0
                elif opt =='/PNEUMONIA/':
                    label = 1
                val_images.append(img)
                val_labels.append(label)
            elif i == 'test':
                if opt =='/NORMAL/':
                    label = 0
                elif opt =='/PNEUMONIA/':
                    label = 1
                test_images.append(img)
                test_labels.append(label)

train_images has all the images required for training. val_images, val_labels, test_images and test_labels contains all images and labels for validation and testing. All these images labels are in the list. Convert this list into numpy arrays

Convolutional Neural Network¶

Building the model¶

In [82]:
from keras.models import Model, Sequential
from keras.layers import Input, Dense, Flatten, Dropout, BatchNormalization
from keras.layers import Conv2D, SeparableConv2D, MaxPool2D, LeakyReLU, Activation
from keras.optimizers import Adam
from keras.preprocessing.image import ImageDataGenerator
from keras.callbacks import ModelCheckpoint, ReduceLROnPlateau, EarlyStopping

# Creating Different Layers of Convolutional Neural Network - Input, hidden, output.

# Input Layer

input_layer = Input(shape = (150, 150, 3))

# Adding first Convolutional layer and Maxpooking
conv1 = Conv2D(filters=16, kernel_size=(3, 3), activation='relu', padding='same')(input_layer)
conv1 = Conv2D(filters=16, kernel_size=(3, 3), activation='relu', padding='same')(conv1)
conv1 = MaxPool2D(pool_size=(2, 2))(conv1)

# Adding second Convolutional layer and Maxpooking
conv2 = SeparableConv2D(filters=32, kernel_size=(3, 3), activation='relu', padding='same')(conv1)
conv2 = SeparableConv2D(filters=32, kernel_size=(3, 3), activation='relu', padding='same')(conv2)
conv2 = BatchNormalization()(conv2)
conv2 = MaxPool2D(pool_size=(2, 2))(conv2)

# Adding third Convolutional layer and Maxpooking
conv3 = SeparableConv2D(filters=64, kernel_size=(3, 3), activation='relu', padding='same')(conv2)
conv3 = SeparableConv2D(filters=64, kernel_size=(3, 3), activation='relu', padding='same')(conv3)
conv3 = BatchNormalization()(conv3)
conv3 = MaxPool2D(pool_size=(2, 2))(conv3)

# Adding fourth Convolutional layer and Maxpooking
conv4 = SeparableConv2D(filters=128, kernel_size=(3, 3), activation='relu', padding='same')(conv3)
conv4 = SeparableConv2D(filters=128, kernel_size=(3, 3), activation='relu', padding='same')(conv4)
conv4 = BatchNormalization()(conv4)
conv4 = MaxPool2D(pool_size=(2, 2))(conv4)
conv4 = Dropout(rate=0.2)(conv4)

# Adding second Convolutional layer and Maxpooking
conv5 = SeparableConv2D(filters=256, kernel_size=(3, 3), activation='relu', padding='same')(conv4)
conv5 = SeparableConv2D(filters=256, kernel_size=(3, 3), activation='relu', padding='same')(conv5)
conv5 = BatchNormalization()(conv5)
conv5 = MaxPool2D(pool_size=(2, 2))(conv5)
conv5 = Dropout(rate=0.2)(conv5)

# Adding Flatten Layer
flat = Flatten()(conv5)

# Adding first hidden layer with 512 neurons
flat = Dense(units=512, activation='relu')(flat)
flat = Dropout(rate=0.7)(flat)

# Adding second hidden layer with 128 neurons
flat = Dense(units=128, activation='relu')(flat)
flat = Dropout(rate=0.5)(flat)

# Adding third hidden layer with 512 neurons
flat = Dense(units=64, activation='relu')(flat)
flat = Dropout(rate=0.3)(flat)

# Layer with output layer of neural network
output = Dense(units=1, activation='sigmoid')(flat)

# Creating model
model = Model(inputs=inputs, outputs=output)

import random

# Function to generate randome index values of specified length
def get_index_list(start, end, num): 
    index_list = [] 
    for i in range(num): 
        index_list.append(random.randint(start, end))   
    return index_list

# Displaying image and its predicted value
image_index = get_index_list(0, 623, 5)
plt.figure(figsize = (10, 10))
for i in range(len(image_index)):
    plt.subplot(2, 5, i + 1)
    plt.imshow(x_test[image_index[i]], cmap = plt.cm.gray_r, interpolation = 'nearest')

from sklearn.metrics import confusion_matrix, classification_report

# Function to plot confusion matrix
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
def get_confusion_matrix(y_test, y_pred):
    import seaborn as sn
    plt.figure(figsize = (6,5))
    sn.heatmap(confusion_matrix(y_test, np.round(y_pred)), cmap="Greens", annot = True)
    plt.xlabel('Predicted Value')
    plt.ylabel('Acual Value')
